### 2. PostgreSQL Schema (DDL)

#### [NEW] [001_initial_schema.sql](file:///d:/projects/IFDC%20asssets%20website/backend/migrations/001_initial_schema.sql)

**Enums:**
- `user_role` → `super_admin`, `admin_manager`, `editor_team_leader`, `user_employee`
- `asset_status` → `available`, `in_use`, `maintenance`, `retired`, `reserved`
- `maintenance_status` → `pending`, `in_progress`, `completed`
- `reservation_status` → `pending`, `approved`, `rejected`, `returned`

**Tables:**

| Table | Purpose | Key Columns |
|---|---|---|
| `departments` | Org structure | `id`, `name`, `description` |
| `users` | All user data + RBAC | `id`, `email`, `password_hash`, `role`, `department_id`, `full_name`, `position`, `phone`, `whatsapp`, `vehicle_license_number`, `vehicle_license_expiry`, `cv_url`, `id_card_url` |
| `drone_assets` | Operation category | `id`, `name`, `serial_number`, `model`, `status`, `department_id`, `total_flight_hours`, `last_maintenance_date`, `next_maintenance_date` |
| `drone_maintenance_logs` | Maintenance history | `id`, `drone_asset_id`, `performed_by`, `status`, `description`, `started_at`, `completed_at` |
| `office_assets` | Office category | `id`, `name`, `category` (furniture/printer/laptop/etc), `serial_number`, `status`, `department_id`, `assigned_to`, `purchase_date`, `warranty_expiry` |
| `rnd_assets` | R&D / V-TOL | `id`, `name`, `asset_type` (vtol/experimental/prototype/component), `serial_number`, `status`, `department_id`, `specifications` (JSONB), `is_classified` |
| `reservations` | Cross-category booking | `id`, `user_id`, `asset_type` (drone/office/rnd), `asset_id`, `status`, `requested_at`, `approved_by`, `approved_at`, `start_date`, `end_date`, `notes` |
| `refresh_tokens` | JWT token management | `id`, `user_id`, `token_hash`, `expires_at`, `revoked` |

All tables include `created_at` / `updated_at` timestamps and proper indexes on foreign keys, emails, serial numbers.

