### 3. Go Backend Implementation

#### [NEW] [main.go](file:///d:/projects/IFDC%20asssets%20website/backend/cmd/server/main.go)
Entry point: loads config, connects to DB, registers routes, starts Gin server.

#### [NEW] [config.go](file:///d:/projects/IFDC%20asssets%20website/backend/internal/config/config.go)
Loads `.env` via `godotenv`; exposes typed `Config` struct with `DB_HOST`, `DB_PORT`, `DB_USER`, `DB_PASSWORD`, `DB_NAME`, `JWT_SECRET`, `JWT_EXPIRY`, `SERVER_PORT`.

#### [NEW] [postgres.go](file:///d:/projects/IFDC%20asssets%20website/backend/internal/database/postgres.go)
Creates and returns a `*sql.DB` pool using `lib/pq`; includes connection retry logic.

#### [NEW] Go Models (`internal/models/`)
Go structs with [json](file:///d:/projects/IFDC%20asssets%20website/frontend/package.json) and `db` tags mapping 1:1 to every table listed above.

#### [NEW] Auth Handler (`internal/handlers/auth.go`)
- `POST /api/auth/register` — hash password (bcrypt), create user, return JWT
- `POST /api/auth/login` — verify credentials, issue access + refresh tokens
- `POST /api/auth/refresh` — validate refresh token, issue new access token

#### [NEW] Auth Middleware (`internal/middleware/auth.go`)
- Extracts `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header
- Validates JWT signature & expiry using `golang-jwt/jwt/v5`
- Injects `userID` and `userRole` into Gin context

#### [NEW] RBAC Middleware (`internal/middleware/rbac.go`)
- `RequireRole(allowedRoles ...string)` — returns a Gin handler that checks if the authenticated user's role is in the allowed set
- Role hierarchy: `super_admin` > `admin_manager` > `editor_team_leader` > `user_employee`

#### [NEW] Routes (`internal/routes/routes.go`)
Route groups with middleware applied per group:
- `/api/auth/*` — public
- `/api/users/*` — `super_admin`, `admin_manager`
- `/api/operations/*` — all authenticated, write restricted
- `/api/office/*` — all authenticated, write restricted
- `/api/rnd/*` — `super_admin`, `admin_manager`, `editor_team_leader`

#### [NEW] [.env.example](file:///d:/projects/IFDC%20asssets%20website/backend/.env.example)
Template with placeholder values for all environment variables.

